254
00:14:53.159 --> 00:14:54.654
We'll keep it on file.

255
00:14:54.678 --> 00:14:56.772
Come with me.

256
00:14:56.796 --> 00:14:58.195
You can control it.

257
00:15:00.666 --> 00:15:01.977
I wish it was true.

258
00:15:02.001 --> 00:15:03.579
Barry. it is.

259
00:15:03.603 --> 00:15:06.048
I can teach you how.

260
00:15:06.072 --> 00:15:08.517
There's enough people
in my brain already.

261
00:15:08.541 --> 00:15:10.452
You're on your own.

262
00:15:10.476 --> 00:15:12.376
Right this way.

263
00:15:29.129 --> 00:15:31.907
I dreamed you were gone.

264
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:34.327
You did?

265
00:15:34.351 --> 00:15:38.136
That's funny. 'cause I was.

266
00:15:41.057 --> 00:15:42.234
Sookie...

267
00:15:42.258 --> 00:15:43.953
It was only for a few minutes.

268
00:15:43.977 --> 00:15:45.387
I had to.

269
00:15:45.411 --> 00:15:47.356
Bill. it's the most
amazing thing.

270
00:15:47.380 --> 00:15:49.675
I met another telepath.

271
00:15:49.699 --> 00:15:53.346
He's not very nice. and
he's not very good at it.

272
00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:57.583
but. oh. it's wonderful knowing
there's somebody besides me.

273
00:15:57.607 --> 00:16:00.720
You made him aware of your
gift after everything I've said?

274
00:16:00.744 --> 00:16:02.388
Not on purpose.

275
00:16:02.412 --> 00:16:05.813
We were in each other's
heads before we knew it.

276
00:16:07.016 --> 00:16:08.861
I thought you'd be happy for me.

277
00:16:08.885 --> 00:16:11.831
The more people
know what you do.

278
00:16:11.855 --> 00:16:13.999
the harder it is for
me to protect you.

279
00:16:14.023 --> 00:16:16.235
He can't even admit
it what he is to himself.

280
00:16:16.259 --> 00:16:17.903
He's not gonna do
any talking about me.

281
00:16:17.927 --> 00:16:20.889
You can't be sure. Yes. I can.

282
00:16:20.913 --> 00:16:22.792
I'm good at this.

283
00:16:22.816 --> 00:16:25.060
Look. if all I'm
supposed to do in Dallas

284
00:16:25.084 --> 00:16:26.495
is shut up and take orders.

285
00:16:26.519 --> 00:16:30.232
I might as well be
slinging beers at Merlotte's.

286
00:16:30.256 --> 00:16:33.386
You're the one who told me
I was more than a waitress.

287
00:16:33.410 --> 00:16:35.237
You are.

288
00:16:35.261 --> 00:16:37.723
But... What?

289
00:16:37.747 --> 00:16:39.976
Never mind.

290
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:43.179
Talk to me.

291
00:16:43.203 --> 00:16:46.804
Lean on me. I've
leaned on you plenty.

292
00:16:48.441 --> 00:16:50.353
Well. here I am.

293
00:16:50.377 --> 00:16:53.356
responsible for you and Jessica.

294
00:16:53.380 --> 00:16:56.292
and yet no decisions are mine.

295
00:16:56.316 --> 00:16:58.127
And it makes me feel...

296
00:16:58.151 --> 00:16:59.934
Like a human?

297
00:17:01.871 --> 00:17:04.499
Like a waitress.

298
00:17:04.523 --> 00:17:07.891
You're walking in my shoes.
and it's giving you blisters.

299
00:17:13.132 --> 00:17:16.767
Eric is strangely
intense about all this.

300
00:17:17.970 --> 00:17:20.082
It's not like him.

301
00:17:20.106 --> 00:17:21.817
I don't trust it.

302
00:17:21.841 --> 00:17:23.719
Don't you worry about Eric.

303
00:17:23.743 --> 00:17:26.439
We'll do the job and go home.

304
00:17:26.463 --> 00:17:29.341
A deal's a deal.

305
00:17:29.365 --> 00:17:32.344
Sookie. you know what he's like.

306
00:17:32.368 --> 00:17:35.614
What's it to him to break
a contract with a girl?

307
00:17:35.638 --> 00:17:37.921
A woman.

308
00:17:40.042 --> 00:17:41.921
He needs me.

309
00:17:41.945 --> 00:17:44.295
He won't want to make me mad.

310
00:17:48.017 --> 00:17:50.379
I can't lose you.

311
00:17:50.403 --> 00:17:53.871
You never will.

312
00:18:03.149 --> 00:18:05.827
Hope you're enjoying
that Co-Cola. Arlene.

313
00:18:05.851 --> 00:18:08.313
Well. thank you. Daphne. I am.

314
00:18:08.337 --> 00:18:12.435
Because unlike you. I actually
did my closing prep last night.

315
00:18:12.459 --> 00:18:15.704
I'd appreciate it if you gave
me a hand. just for today.

316
00:18:15.728 --> 00:18:17.640
ARLENE: Then you'll never learn.

317
00:18:17.664 --> 00:18:20.058
Now. some people around
here might let you slide on by.

318
00:18:20.082 --> 00:18:22.994
but I'm thinking about
your future as a server.

319
00:18:23.018 --> 00:18:25.281
That's real generous.

320
00:18:25.305 --> 00:18:28.417
Don't forget to
make the iced tea.

321
00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:30.786
Hey. good-looking.

322
00:18:30.810 --> 00:18:33.444
Hey. you.

323
00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:39.128
Terry. could you make
the iced tea for me. please?

324
00:18:39.152 --> 00:18:41.964
Don't you do it. Please?

325
00:18:41.988 --> 00:18:43.682
Uh...

326
00:18:43.706 --> 00:18:46.034
You better not.

327
00:18:46.058 --> 00:18:47.724
[GROANS]

328
00:18:49.345 --> 00:18:50.606
Why the hell are y'all

329
00:18:50.630 --> 00:18:53.714
putting me through this
crap? See what you did?

330
00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:59.498
Mean old freckle-faced
redheaded witch.

331
00:18:59.522 --> 00:19:01.766
Good morning. Daphne.

332
00:19:01.790 --> 00:19:04.241
Back at you. boss.

333
00:19:08.848 --> 00:19:11.693
Hey. why'd you
take off last night?

334
00:19:11.717 --> 00:19:14.196
I looked everywhere for you.

335
00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:16.298
I just went for a little run.

336
00:19:16.322 --> 00:19:19.335
You know. I always seem
to need one after a shift.

337
00:19:19.359 --> 00:19:20.959
SAM: Hey. me too.

338
00:19:22.628 --> 00:19:25.641
I reckon you had all you could
handle for one night anyway.

339
00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:27.760
I reckon you underestimate me.

340
00:19:27.784 --> 00:19:29.562
Guess we'll find out.

341
00:19:29.586 --> 00:19:32.064
When?

342
00:19:32.088 --> 00:19:35.205
Soon. Better be.

343
00:19:37.059 --> 00:19:39.772
Lafayette!

344
00:19:39.796 --> 00:19:41.874
[ARLENE LAUGHING]

345
00:19:41.898 --> 00:19:45.711
Oh. Terry. Lafayette's back.

346
00:19:45.735 --> 00:19:48.797
Thank God. brother. Thank God.

347
00:19:48.821 --> 00:19:50.321
Can we talk?

348
00:19:58.297 --> 00:20:02.333
Where the fuck have you been?

349
00:20:04.470 --> 00:20:07.132
Couldn't pick up a damn phone?

350
00:20:07.156 --> 00:20:08.800
Sorry.

351
00:20:08.824 --> 00:20:10.435
Well. sorry's not good enough.

352
00:20:10.459 --> 00:20:12.036
Not only did you
leave us high and dry.

353
00:20:12.060 --> 00:20:16.408
but there are people here
who give a shit about you.

354
00:20:16.432 --> 00:20:19.166
We didn't know if you
were alive or dead.

355
00:20:23.723 --> 00:20:25.601
Wait. ordinarily.
right about now.

356
00:20:25.625 --> 00:20:27.002
you'd be telling me to fuck off

357
00:20:27.026 --> 00:20:29.710
in some colorful
and creative way.

358
00:20:32.131 --> 00:20:36.428
Well. you want to
talk. do some talking.

359
00:20:36.452 --> 00:20:38.864
Sam.

360
00:20:38.888 --> 00:20:42.585
all I want to know is.
can I have my job back?

361
00:20:42.609 --> 00:20:44.720
I ought to tell you to fuck off.

362
00:20:44.744 --> 00:20:46.121
All that pressure in the kitchen

363
00:20:46.145 --> 00:20:49.212
just about put Terry
back in the VA hospital.

364
00:20:52.452 --> 00:20:55.063
Yeah. of course you
can have your job back.

365
00:20:55.087 --> 00:20:57.407
The place ain't the
same without you.

366
00:20:59.558 --> 00:21:03.171
Thank you. Sam.

367
00:21:03.195 --> 00:21:04.695
Lafayette.

368
00:21:09.001 --> 00:21:10.984
What happened to you?

369
00:21:25.818 --> 00:21:28.847
GABE: It's midnight.
You're out of ammo.

370
00:21:28.871 --> 00:21:31.983
You got five hungry
vampires snapping at your ass.

371
00:21:32.007 --> 00:21:33.440
What are you gonna do?

372
00:21:34.594 --> 00:21:36.972
What are you gonna do? MEN: Run.

373
00:21:36.996 --> 00:21:38.557
Run fast.

374
00:21:38.581 --> 00:21:40.875
[GRUNTING]

375
00:21:40.899 --> 00:21:42.978
JASON: Whoa. whoa. get up.

376
00:21:43.002 --> 00:21:44.446
You gotta keep going. Guy.

377
00:21:44.470 --> 00:21:46.448
Five hungry. snapping vampires.

378
00:21:46.472 --> 00:21:49.451
Fuck it. I hate this. I just
want to be a bank teller again.

379
00:21:49.475 --> 00:21:52.309
That's fine. dude. Let
the vampires chew you up.

380
00:21:53.730 --> 00:21:56.046
You're not good enough
to lead for the Lord.

381
00:21:57.266 --> 00:21:59.962
That's how you
do it. Stackhouse.

382
00:21:59.986 --> 00:22:01.330
You better pace yourself.

383
00:22:01.354 --> 00:22:03.999
This is my pace. Whoo!

384
00:22:04.023 --> 00:22:05.050
Asshole.

385
00:22:05.074 --> 00:22:07.074
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]

386
00:22:16.369 --> 00:22:19.048
Are you still here?
Or did you come back?

387
00:22:19.072 --> 00:22:22.568
Karl and I slept over.
Don't you remember?

388
00:22:22.592 --> 00:22:25.470
Maybe not. You were
having a very nice time.

389
00:22:25.494 --> 00:22:27.839
Maybe not. What's all this?

390
00:22:27.863 --> 00:22:31.393
Oh. looks like we
need a place to stay.

391
00:22:31.417 --> 00:22:34.413
Stay today? Stay tonight?

392
00:22:34.437 --> 00:22:36.915
Eh. Little while.

393
00:22:36.939 --> 00:22:38.500
But you have your own home.

394
00:22:38.524 --> 00:22:40.869
That's not mine.

395
00:22:40.893 --> 00:22:43.505
What? It belongs
to one of my clients.

396
00:22:43.529 --> 00:22:45.840
He was out of the country.
but he's back this morning.

397
00:22:45.864 --> 00:22:47.543
I'm sure I told you. no?

398
00:22:47.567 --> 00:22:50.979
No. You... You didn't. Hm.

399
00:22:51.003 --> 00:22:53.048
Look. I-I hate to tell you this.

400
00:22:53.072 --> 00:22:57.002
but this isn't gonna work.

401
00:22:57.026 --> 00:22:58.670
But I assumed...

402
00:22:58.694 --> 00:23:01.857
I mean. we've all been
so happy living together.

403
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:03.826
That you'd want
to have us close.

404
00:23:03.850 --> 00:23:05.894
Maryann. I'm a
guest here myself.

405
00:23:05.918 --> 00:23:07.796
I can't be having a
house full of people

406
00:23:07.820 --> 00:23:09.064
Sookie doesn't even know.

407
00:23:09.088 --> 00:23:10.899
She wouldn't mind.

408
00:23:10.923 --> 00:23:13.068
You explain how
much we mean to you.

409
00:23:13.092 --> 00:23:15.370
Don't get me wrong. I
couldn't be more grateful

410
00:23:15.394 --> 00:23:18.473
for everything
you've done. but...

411
00:23:18.497 --> 00:23:22.077
I don't feel right about this.

412
00:23:22.101 --> 00:23:25.547
You can't move in.

413
00:23:25.571 --> 00:23:27.716
I'm sorry.

414
00:23:27.740 --> 00:23:31.475
Oh. I see. Okay.

415
00:23:38.367 --> 00:23:40.812
[PLAYING GUITAR]

416
00:23:40.836 --> 00:23:43.515
Did you know Maryann wants
us all to be roommates here?

417
00:23:43.539 --> 00:23:45.717
Cool. I guess that other
guy came back from Peru.

418
00:23:45.741 --> 00:23:49.104
No. not cool. Not gonna
happen. I just moved in.

419
00:23:49.128 --> 00:23:52.775
Okay. fine. we can go somewhere
else. if that's how you feel.

420
00:23:52.799 --> 00:23:56.178
That's all you got to say?

421
00:23:56.202 --> 00:23:57.612
Relax. It's no big deal.

422
00:23:57.636 --> 00:24:00.315
What...? What are you.
nomads? Fucking Bedouins?

423
00:24:00.339 --> 00:24:02.284
We move around a bit.
Nothing wrong with that.

424
00:24:02.308 --> 00:24:04.920
Nothing except I didn't
know. You could've told me.

425
00:24:04.944 --> 00:24:07.689
Who cares? What matters is
being with the people you love.

426
00:24:07.713 --> 00:24:09.124
Well. other things matter too.

427
00:24:09.148 --> 00:24:11.459
Like knowing the truth
about the people you love.

428
00:24:11.483 --> 00:24:12.828
So while we're on the subject.

429
00:24:12.852 --> 00:24:16.253
what exactly is your
thing with Maryann?

430
00:24:17.690 --> 00:24:19.501
Well. when I was ready
to lay down and die.

431
00:24:19.525 --> 00:24:21.186
she lifted me up.
same as she did you.

432
00:24:21.210 --> 00:24:22.855
Now you follow her
wherever she goes?

433
00:24:22.879 --> 00:24:25.607
I'm not her dog. if that's
what you're trying to say.

434
00:24:25.631 --> 00:24:28.977
And why all of a sudden are
you so paranoid about Maryann?

435
00:24:29.001 --> 00:24:31.363
Because I'm trying
not to be a fool.

436
00:24:31.387 --> 00:24:33.899
Know what this is really about?
Your history is so fucked up.

437
00:24:33.923 --> 00:24:36.151
you have no clue what family is.

438
00:24:36.175 --> 00:24:38.620
That's not fair.

439
00:24:38.644 --> 00:24:41.990
I do have a clue.

440
00:24:42.014 --> 00:24:44.026
Sort of.

441
00:24:44.050 --> 00:24:46.462
Kind of.

442
00:24:46.486 --> 00:24:49.197
Who gives a damn about a house?

443
00:24:49.221 --> 00:24:51.767
Maryann. Karl and me.
we take care of each other.

444
00:24:51.791 --> 00:24:53.307
We took care of you.

445
00:24:55.995 --> 00:24:58.629
That's family. Tara.

446
00:25:04.587 --> 00:25:07.149
How are we gonna work
on our defensive tactics

447
00:25:07.173 --> 00:25:08.916
if we can't even climb a fence?

448
00:25:08.940 --> 00:25:11.253
Let's go. Next. come on.

449
00:25:11.277 --> 00:25:14.010
Go on. Come on.

450
00:25:15.614 --> 00:25:19.161
Get up there. get up
there. Let's go. come on.

451
00:25:19.185 --> 00:25:20.328
Come on.

452
00:25:20.352 --> 00:25:22.063
See? You should
have paced yourself.

453
00:25:22.087 --> 00:25:24.415
If you're laying down.
you better be dead.

454
00:25:24.439 --> 00:25:26.768
Stand up.

455
00:25:26.792 --> 00:25:28.203
Come on.

456
00:25:28.227 --> 00:25:29.922
Why do you embarrass me?

457
00:25:29.946 --> 00:25:32.257
Why do you straight-out
embarrass me?

458
00:25:32.281 --> 00:25:35.177
What's your name. failure?

459
00:25:35.201 --> 00:25:37.963
LUKE: Luke. It's Luke.

460
00:25:37.987 --> 00:25:41.649
Well. Luke. your entire family
has been ambushed by vampires.

461
00:25:41.673 --> 00:25:46.355
and they're bleeding to death
on the other side of this fence.

462
00:25:46.379 --> 00:25:48.857
No. Yeah. Yeah. they are.

463
00:25:48.881 --> 00:25:52.394
Your mama and daddy are
drowning in buckets of their own blood

464
00:25:52.418 --> 00:25:55.864
calling your name. It's
gonna be over in 30 seconds.

465
00:25:55.888 --> 00:25:57.449
Let's go.

466
00:25:57.473 --> 00:25:59.751
Nice work. Luke.

467
00:25:59.775 --> 00:26:01.236
They're gone. Massacred.

468
00:26:01.260 --> 00:26:03.971
You'll never see them again.
and it's your own damn fault.

469
00:26:03.995 --> 00:26:05.456
Stay right there. LUKE: I tried.

470
00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:08.426
Now what are you gonna do?

471
00:26:08.450 --> 00:26:09.878
He's a big fat loser.

472
00:26:09.902 --> 00:26:12.748
He's brought shame on
himself. shame on you.

473
00:26:12.772 --> 00:26:14.249
and shame on his religion.

474
00:26:14.273 --> 00:26:16.251
What's a real leader gonna do?

475
00:26:16.275 --> 00:26:18.541
LUKE: Just get rid of me.

476
00:26:19.579 --> 00:26:21.790
Just leave me.

477
00:26:21.814 --> 00:26:23.425
Up to you.

478
00:26:23.449 --> 00:26:26.567
[♪♪♪]

479
00:26:32.607 --> 00:26:35.003
Luke. look at me.

480
00:26:35.027 --> 00:26:38.073
Hey.

481
00:26:38.097 --> 00:26:40.909
It's only a damn fence. Come on.

482
00:26:40.933 --> 00:26:44.484
Come on.

483
00:26:46.305 --> 00:26:47.999
I got you. brother.

484
00:26:48.023 --> 00:26:50.819
[GRUNTS]

485
00:26:50.843 --> 00:26:54.272
It's not too late.

486
00:26:54.296 --> 00:26:56.230
You're gonna save your family.

487
00:26:57.483 --> 00:26:59.845
Now that's a fricking
soldier of God.

488
00:26:59.869 --> 00:27:00.912
[SARAH CLAPPING]

489
00:27:00.936 --> 00:27:03.315
Good job. SARAH:
Good job. Jason.

490
00:27:03.339 --> 00:27:04.600
Praise his light.

491
00:27:04.624 --> 00:27:06.768
Whoo!

492
00:27:06.792 --> 00:27:08.070
Whoo! Good work.

493
00:27:08.094 --> 00:27:10.389
GABE: Next. Let's go.
let's go. Come on. guys.

494
00:27:10.413 --> 00:27:12.413
[♪♪♪]

495
00:27:14.583 --> 00:27:17.962
MAN: You should have told me
Eric hired a fucking human. Isabel.

496
00:27:17.986 --> 00:27:20.032
Now. wait just a minute.

497
00:27:20.056 --> 00:27:21.799
Respect her. Thank you.

498
00:27:21.823 --> 00:27:23.201
I couldn't tell you. Stan.

499
00:27:23.225 --> 00:27:24.902
You've been off on
your own for days.

500
00:27:24.926 --> 00:27:27.539
Are you certain Godric was
abducted by the Fellowship?

501
00:27:27.563 --> 00:27:28.991
Yes. No.

502
00:27:29.015 --> 00:27:31.493
They're the only ones with
the organization and manpower.

503
00:27:31.517 --> 00:27:33.995
But they're amateurs. It
doesn't make any sense.

504
00:27:34.019 --> 00:27:36.881
This is Godric we're talking
about. 2000 years old.

505
00:27:36.905 --> 00:27:39.584
STAN: Old don't make you
smart. [MOUTHS]<i> Two thousand?</i>

506
00:27:39.608 --> 00:27:41.586
Besides. there's no proof.

507
00:27:41.610 --> 00:27:44.839
If they've got him. I'll
hear it. That's my job.

508
00:27:44.863 --> 00:27:47.359
There's no reason to wait.

509
00:27:47.383 --> 00:27:50.111
We need to take these
fanatics down. Full-out attack.

510
00:27:50.135 --> 00:27:53.548
Exterminate them like the
vermin they are. leave no trace.

511
00:27:53.572 --> 00:27:57.419
Hm. Vampire-hating church
annihilated. Wonder who did it?

512
00:27:57.443 --> 00:27:58.687
Fucking brilliant.

513
00:27:58.711 --> 00:28:01.056
I doubt the king of Texas
would approve the destruction

514
00:28:01.080 --> 00:28:02.974
of our international
political agenda.

515
00:28:02.998 --> 00:28:04.609
Fuck that.

516
00:28:04.633 --> 00:28:07.511
The Great Revelation is the
biggest mistake we ever made.

517
00:28:07.535 --> 00:28:10.882
Don't use Godric to make
your own little power play.

518
00:28:10.906 --> 00:28:13.256
You're completely incompetent.

519
00:28:14.810 --> 00:28:15.903
What's happened to Godric

520
00:28:15.927 --> 00:28:17.589
that he surrounds
himself with clowns?

521
00:28:17.613 --> 00:28:20.408
We invited you as a courtesy.

522
00:28:20.432 --> 00:28:23.679
This is not your territory.
You have no voice here.

523
00:28:23.703 --> 00:28:25.597
STAN: Yeah. sheriff.

524
00:28:25.621 --> 00:28:27.632
Why don't you run on
back down to Louisiana?

525
00:28:27.656 --> 00:28:29.234
We don't need you
or your puppets.

526
00:28:29.258 --> 00:28:31.986
Oh. I'm not going anywhere.
And I'm nobody's puppet.

527
00:28:32.010 --> 00:28:33.939
What we need is a plan.

528
00:28:33.963 --> 00:28:35.073
I have a plan.

529
00:28:35.097 --> 00:28:37.025
It's not a plan. it's a movie.

530
00:28:37.049 --> 00:28:41.335
It's not a movie. it's a war.

531
00:28:42.888 --> 00:28:45.021
Idiots.

532
00:28:50.062 --> 00:28:51.740
NEWLIN: I'm in the
middle of something.

533
00:28:51.764 --> 00:28:54.175
You can't come in here
when I'm in front of my people.

534
00:28:54.199 --> 00:28:55.911
SARAH: I wanna
talk to you about it.

535
00:28:55.935 --> 00:28:57.645
How can I get them
to respect me...?

536
00:28:57.669 --> 00:28:59.080
We are supposed to be partners.

537
00:28:59.104 --> 00:29:00.282
We are partners.

538
00:29:00.306 --> 00:29:02.250
Then why does Gabe
always know more than I do?

539
00:29:02.274 --> 00:29:04.052
I don't have time for this.

540
00:29:04.076 --> 00:29:06.471
You mean you don't
have time for me.

541
00:29:06.495 --> 00:29:08.973
This is very valuable
information. Gabe.

542
00:29:08.997 --> 00:29:10.174
It's excellent work.

543
00:29:10.198 --> 00:29:12.711
I told both of you I
don't care for this.

544
00:29:12.735 --> 00:29:14.879
You're going too darn far.

545
00:29:14.903 --> 00:29:17.582
Thank you. Reverend Newlin.
I'll. uh. put things in motion.

546
00:29:17.606 --> 00:29:18.683
Thanks.

547
00:29:18.707 --> 00:29:20.585
You don't listen to
me at all anymore.

548
00:29:20.609 --> 00:29:21.937
NEWLIN: What?

549
00:29:21.961 --> 00:29:23.905
Jason.

550
00:29:23.929 --> 00:29:25.407
Oh. Uh. you wanted me?

551
00:29:25.431 --> 00:29:28.342
Yes. You were fantastic today.

552
00:29:28.366 --> 00:29:30.328
Steve. he was such a warrior.

553
00:29:30.352 --> 00:29:33.097
So you said. I'm impressed.

554
00:29:33.121 --> 00:29:35.033
You're rising to the
next level. recruit.

555
00:29:35.057 --> 00:29:37.953
I am? Well. what's that?

556
00:29:37.977 --> 00:29:40.822
Come take a little walk with me.

557
00:29:40.846 --> 00:29:42.958
I'll go too. We got it. honey.

558
00:29:42.982 --> 00:29:46.783
I'm going to show you something
that very few people have seen.

559
00:29:52.374 --> 00:29:54.986
Man to man? Sometimes
I almost understand

560
00:29:55.010 --> 00:29:56.787
why some people
believe in divorce.

561
00:29:56.811 --> 00:29:58.489
But you got Sarah. Yeah.

562
00:29:58.513 --> 00:30:01.726
I got her even when I don't
want her. Heh. heh. heh.

563
00:30:01.750 --> 00:30:03.761
Oh. you know I'm just kidding.

564
00:30:03.785 --> 00:30:05.864
All right. you ready? Yes. sir.

565
00:30:05.888 --> 00:30:10.485
Light of Day Institute
Research and Development.

566
00:30:10.509 --> 00:30:12.120
Holy sh...

567
00:30:12.144 --> 00:30:13.905
Holiness.

568
00:30:13.929 --> 00:30:15.640
[CHUCKLING]

569
00:30:15.664 --> 00:30:18.009
Yeah. We're not exactly sure yet

570
00:30:18.033 --> 00:30:19.411
of all the ways
to take them out.

571
00:30:19.435 --> 00:30:21.279
At first. we just
focused on the guns.

572
00:30:21.303 --> 00:30:25.050
but then we thought. "Well.
hey. what's a wooden arrow?"

573
00:30:25.074 --> 00:30:26.884
Well. it's an itty-bitty stake.

574
00:30:26.908 --> 00:30:28.253
That's right. Jason.

575
00:30:28.277 --> 00:30:31.088
An itty-bitty stake to drive
through a vampire's dead.

576
00:30:31.112 --> 00:30:33.809
rotten heart at 324
feet per second.

577
00:30:33.833 --> 00:30:35.376
And that's all she wrote.

578
00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:37.312
I got silver bullets.

579
00:30:37.336 --> 00:30:39.815
silver bullets with holy
water. wooden bullets.

580
00:30:39.839 --> 00:30:41.699
We talked about those. Yes. sir.

581
00:30:41.723 --> 00:30:44.352
A flamethrower. Whoa. man.

582
00:30:44.376 --> 00:30:46.821
Silver throwing stars.

583
00:30:46.845 --> 00:30:50.659
Now. that I wouldn't
have thought of.

584
00:30:50.683 --> 00:30:52.861
[GRUNTS]

585
00:30:52.885 --> 00:30:54.229
Decapitation might work.

586
00:30:54.253 --> 00:30:58.149
so. uh. we got a guillotine
on order. just in case.

587
00:30:58.173 --> 00:30:59.334
What...?

588
00:30:59.358 --> 00:31:02.236
Oh. that's a machine
like a giant razor.

589
00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:05.006
Shwoop. Cuts
the heads right off.

590
00:31:05.030 --> 00:31:06.708
Shwoop.

591
00:31:06.732 --> 00:31:08.559
Yeah. I bet that'd
do it. all right.

592
00:31:08.583 --> 00:31:09.694
There's one good thing

593
00:31:09.718 --> 00:31:11.929
about having these
hell beasts among us:

594
00:31:11.953 --> 00:31:15.366
We'll find better
ways to kill 'em.

595
00:31:15.390 --> 00:31:17.735
[CHUCKLES]

596
00:31:17.759 --> 00:31:20.927
Amen. Amen.

597
00:31:26.501 --> 00:31:29.719
Keep it running.
We're not going in.

598
00:31:34.760 --> 00:31:36.760
[♪♪♪]

599
00:31:44.303 --> 00:31:46.164
You wanna give me
your orders. please?

600
00:31:46.188 --> 00:31:48.866
We already gave our
orders to that other girl. twice.

601
00:31:48.890 --> 00:31:50.502
Sorry. she sucks.

602
00:31:50.526 --> 00:31:53.271
And what's with that fool
bartender? Where's our beers?

603
00:31:53.295 --> 00:31:55.774
Ugh. Tara!

604
00:31:55.798 --> 00:31:58.426
You don't need any beers.
Your butt's as big as a barn.

605
00:31:58.450 --> 00:32:00.828
Well. you look like
you're pregnant.

606
00:32:00.852 --> 00:32:02.480
Nice of you to show
up for work tonight.

607
00:32:02.504 --> 00:32:04.015
I said I was sorry.

608
00:32:04.039 --> 00:32:06.801
I would have got fired.
Lucky you slept with the boss.

609
00:32:06.825 --> 00:32:10.038
Arlene. Tara. step up your game.

610
00:32:10.062 --> 00:32:11.306
We're way behind.

611
00:32:11.330 --> 00:32:13.508
Arlene. don't make me
fire you for talking trash.

612
00:32:13.532 --> 00:32:15.844
You be nice to her.
Sam. It's Tara's fault.

613
00:32:15.868 --> 00:32:18.346
What's my fault?
Sleeping where you eat.

614
00:32:18.370 --> 00:32:21.583
Jesus Christ. Terry.
what'd I ever do to you?

615
00:32:21.607 --> 00:32:24.119
You leave him alone.
And give me my beers.

616
00:32:24.143 --> 00:32:26.621
You know what? Here they are.

617
00:32:26.645 --> 00:32:28.506
Fuck you very
much. Fuck you too.

618
00:32:28.530 --> 00:32:32.059
DAPHNE: Okay. I'm
gonna go just get my...

619
00:32:32.083 --> 00:32:33.377
Son of a... Go. Daphne.

620
00:32:33.401 --> 00:32:34.779
Bitch!

621
00:32:34.803 --> 00:32:37.499
Congratulations. Arlene.
You're Merlotte's best waitress.

622
00:32:37.523 --> 00:32:39.100
Frankly. I aim a little higher.

623
00:32:39.124 --> 00:32:42.053
Well. aim the plates for
the tables. That's all I ask.

624
00:32:42.077 --> 00:32:44.672
Hope I'm nicer to
people when I'm your age.

625
00:32:44.696 --> 00:32:46.641
Tara. how freaking
long do I have to wait

626
00:32:46.665 --> 00:32:49.477
for my 7 and 7. diet and rum.
two Scotches and a screwdriver?

627
00:32:49.501 --> 00:32:51.245
You never gave me
that order. I was here.

628
00:32:51.269 --> 00:32:52.547
You weren't paying attention.

629
00:32:52.571 --> 00:32:53.881
No. you weren't. and yes. I was.

630
00:32:53.905 --> 00:32:55.650
What's the holdup on my tequila?

631
00:32:55.674 --> 00:32:57.152
You never asked
me for any tequi...

632
00:32:57.176 --> 00:32:59.120
You know. I think
Tara's on drugs.

633
00:32:59.144 --> 00:33:01.372
Tara. you high? I wish I was.

634
00:33:01.396 --> 00:33:02.741
the way everybody's dogging me.

635
00:33:02.765 --> 00:33:03.841
Tara. Tara.

636
00:33:03.865 --> 00:33:05.043
Tara. Tara.

637
00:33:05.067 --> 00:33:06.310
Tara.

638
00:33:06.334 --> 00:33:08.001
Fuck all of y'all!

639
00:33:11.673 --> 00:33:14.507
SAM: Lafayette. get out my way.

640
00:33:20.482 --> 00:33:22.999
We're done.

641
00:33:27.539 --> 00:33:29.539
[WATER SPLASHING]

642
00:33:44.857 --> 00:33:46.334
[DOOR CLOSES]

643
00:33:46.358 --> 00:33:49.676
Get on out of here.
Bathtub's occupied.

644
00:33:51.530 --> 00:33:53.775
I know.

645
00:33:53.799 --> 00:33:55.715
Sarah?

646
00:33:57.486 --> 00:33:59.430
Did I stay too long?

647
00:33:59.454 --> 00:34:00.882
Do you want me to leave?

648
00:34:00.906 --> 00:34:03.740
Please don't.

649
00:34:12.267 --> 00:34:13.666
I'll help you.

650
00:34:53.708 --> 00:34:55.475
[MOANS]

651
00:35:01.199 --> 00:35:06.014
Mary Magdalene
washed the feet of Jesus.

652
00:35:06.038 --> 00:35:08.771
and dried 'em with her hair.

653
00:35:10.342 --> 00:35:12.676
Isn't that lovely?

654
00:35:13.761 --> 00:35:16.541
Yeah.

655
00:35:16.565 --> 00:35:20.211
We... But wasn't she. like. a...

656
00:35:20.235 --> 00:35:21.930
hooker?

657
00:35:21.954 --> 00:35:25.255
She was not.

658
00:35:27.592 --> 00:35:31.039
Everybody thinks so. but...

659
00:35:31.063 --> 00:35:32.696
that's not in the Bible.

660
00:35:37.953 --> 00:35:41.187
She admired Jesus.

661
00:35:43.091 --> 00:35:45.642
She loved him.

662
00:35:48.079 --> 00:35:50.146
And she wanted to show him.

663
00:35:59.925 --> 00:36:02.069
No.

664
00:36:02.093 --> 00:36:03.671
You don't mean it.

665
00:36:03.695 --> 00:36:05.739
No. I don't.

666
00:36:05.763 --> 00:36:08.547
but I ought to.

667
00:36:09.785 --> 00:36:11.818
Do you know what I think?

668
00:36:16.641 --> 00:36:20.471
I think that after
all your trials...

669
00:36:20.495 --> 00:36:24.063
heartache and pain...

670
00:36:25.533 --> 00:36:28.663
God wants you to have a reward.

671
00:36:28.687 --> 00:36:31.154
Are you sure?

672
00:36:33.958 --> 00:36:38.495
Let me reward you. Jason.

673
00:36:43.902 --> 00:36:47.048
Let me help you find
your way back to joy.

674
00:36:47.072 --> 00:36:49.072
[BOTH PANTING]

675
00:36:51.293 --> 00:36:53.293
[BOTH MOANING]

676
00:37:00.335 --> 00:37:03.714
STAN: We take them all out
at once. Pre-emptive strike.

677
00:37:03.738 --> 00:37:05.733
Of course. so the federal
government can bomb us

678
00:37:05.757 --> 00:37:07.068
back into the Middle Ages.

679
00:37:07.092 --> 00:37:08.436
Things were better then.

680
00:37:08.460 --> 00:37:11.990
Then go to Romania and live
in a cave. you ranchero poser.

681
00:37:12.014 --> 00:37:13.408
[YELLS] [GLASS SHATTERS]

682
00:37:13.432 --> 00:37:15.810
Godric has protected
you. made you rich.

683
00:37:15.834 --> 00:37:18.262
and you stand here spitting
and scratching like infants.

684
00:37:18.286 --> 00:37:20.915
Don't any of you care that
there's a traitor in your midst?

685
00:37:20.939 --> 00:37:22.417
No. Impossible.

686
00:37:22.441 --> 00:37:24.552
Someone tried to kidnap
me from the airport.

687
00:37:24.576 --> 00:37:26.721
You were the only ones
that knew she was coming.

688
00:37:26.745 --> 00:37:28.957
Explain.

689
00:37:28.981 --> 00:37:30.575
Unless it was you.
Unless it was you.

690
00:37:30.599 --> 00:37:31.892
Look. if y'all argue anymore.

691
00:37:31.916 --> 00:37:33.695
I'm gonna fall asleep
or start screaming.

692
00:37:33.719 --> 00:37:36.481
so this is what we're gonna do:

693
00:37:36.505 --> 00:37:38.600
I'll infiltrate the
Fellowship of the Sun.

694
00:37:38.624 --> 00:37:40.485
Absolutely not.

695
00:37:40.509 --> 00:37:42.820
Let her speak.

696
00:37:42.844 --> 00:37:45.189
Bill glamoured the kidnapper.
no one knows who I am.

697
00:37:45.213 --> 00:37:47.809
I'll join the church.
check out their thoughts.

698
00:37:47.833 --> 00:37:50.445
No. During the day.
none of us can help you.

699
00:37:50.469 --> 00:37:53.485
It'll only take a little while.
Really. Bill. It's simple.

700
00:37:54.556 --> 00:37:56.655
Waste of time...

701
00:37:57.993 --> 00:38:00.704
when we could drink them all.

702
00:38:00.728 --> 00:38:03.529
I want no part of this.

703
00:38:05.200 --> 00:38:07.545
There's no easier way to
find out if they're involved.

704
00:38:07.569 --> 00:38:09.313
If it leads us to
Godric. we'll do it.

705
00:38:09.337 --> 00:38:11.521
[DOOR SLAMS]
The decision is made.

706
00:38:14.910 --> 00:38:16.242
A few words.

707
00:38:25.220 --> 00:38:27.115
So tell me.

708
00:38:27.139 --> 00:38:30.306
how goes your
human-vampire relationship?

709
00:38:35.614 --> 00:38:38.425
You knew it would come to this.

710
00:38:38.449 --> 00:38:40.127
She was just clawed and poisoned

711
00:38:40.151 --> 00:38:42.964
by a creature we don't
know and we can't find.

712
00:38:42.988 --> 00:38:45.433
and now. in Dallas.
you're playing with her life.

713
00:38:45.457 --> 00:38:47.835
It's no game to me.

714
00:38:47.859 --> 00:38:50.137
All this for a colleague?

715
00:38:50.161 --> 00:38:52.573
For the sheriff of Area 9?

716
00:38:52.597 --> 00:38:54.147
Why?

717
00:38:57.202 --> 00:39:00.203
[PANTING AND GRUNTING]

718
00:39:03.342 --> 00:39:05.324
[BIRD CAWS]

719
00:39:11.216 --> 00:39:15.096
[IN SWEDISH] Go on.

720
00:39:15.120 --> 00:39:17.854
I'm finished.

721
00:39:20.025 --> 00:39:22.269
Go on.

722
00:39:22.293 --> 00:39:25.555
[IN SWEDISH] No.

723
00:39:25.579 --> 00:39:27.758
[IN SWEDISH] Eric...

724
00:39:27.782 --> 00:39:31.417
you saved our lives
a hundred times.

725
00:39:34.122 --> 00:39:36.400
We won't leave you
to be eaten by wolves.

726
00:39:36.424 --> 00:39:39.721
GUNNAR: We'll wait
for the end by your side.

727
00:39:39.745 --> 00:39:43.057
HROLF: We'll give
you a hero's farewell.

728
00:39:43.081 --> 00:39:47.261
The gods wait
for you in Valhalla.

729
00:39:47.285 --> 00:39:51.098
There will be a party with meat

730
00:39:51.122 --> 00:39:55.118
and gold and beer.

731
00:39:55.142 --> 00:39:58.360
And women? Will there be women?

732
00:40:00.298 --> 00:40:04.245
Wherever I am...

733
00:40:04.269 --> 00:40:06.914
there will always be women.

734
00:40:06.938 --> 00:40:09.205
[GUNNAR & HROLF LAUGHING]

735
00:40:20.785 --> 00:40:22.785
[GRUNTING]

736
00:40:30.328 --> 00:40:32.328
[RUSTLING]

737
00:40:44.009 --> 00:40:46.142
All will be well.

738
00:40:48.029 --> 00:40:50.608
Don't be afraid.

739
00:40:50.632 --> 00:40:54.445
I'm not afraid.

740
00:40:54.469 --> 00:40:56.246
I'm pissed off.

741
00:40:56.270 --> 00:40:58.399
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

742
00:40:58.423 --> 00:41:00.084
Who's there?

743
00:41:00.108 --> 00:41:04.705
[♪♪♪]

744
00:41:04.729 --> 00:41:07.041
Show yourself!

745
00:41:07.065 --> 00:41:09.543
[GRUNTING]

746
00:41:09.567 --> 00:41:11.584
[GRUNTING]

747
00:41:19.077 --> 00:41:21.927
Are you Death?

748
00:41:23.615 --> 00:41:25.681
[IN SWEDISH] I am.

749
00:41:27.051 --> 00:41:30.898
But you're just a little boy.

750
00:41:30.922 --> 00:41:34.185
I'm not.

751
00:41:34.209 --> 00:41:36.053
My men...

752
00:41:36.077 --> 00:41:38.723
Dead.

753
00:41:38.747 --> 00:41:41.147
You swine.

754
00:41:45.770 --> 00:41:50.484
I watched you on the
battlefield last night.

755
00:41:50.508 --> 00:41:54.643
I never saw anyone
fight like you.

756
00:41:56.748 --> 00:42:00.260
I would fight you
now if I could.

757
00:42:00.284 --> 00:42:02.280
[CHUCKLES]

758
00:42:02.304 --> 00:42:04.637
I know.

759
00:42:06.341 --> 00:42:09.241
It's beautiful.

760
00:42:11.613 --> 00:42:14.492
What are you waiting for?

761
00:42:14.516 --> 00:42:16.649
Kill me.

762
00:42:20.705 --> 00:42:25.385
Could you be a
companion of Death?

763
00:42:25.409 --> 00:42:29.924
Could you walk with
me through the world...

764
00:42:29.948 --> 00:42:31.592
through the dark?

765
00:42:31.616 --> 00:42:34.867
I'll teach you all I know.

766
00:42:36.471 --> 00:42:40.050
I'll be your father...

767
00:42:40.074 --> 00:42:44.310
your brother. your child.

768
00:42:48.983 --> 00:42:52.552
What's in it for me?

769
00:42:55.156 --> 00:42:57.934
What you love most:

770
00:42:57.958 --> 00:43:00.459
Life.

771
00:43:02.530 --> 00:43:04.546
Life.

772
00:43:08.352 --> 00:43:10.764
[SLURPING]

773
00:43:10.788 --> 00:43:12.788
[GRUNTING]

774
00:43:21.599 --> 00:43:24.734
Godric is my maker.

775
00:43:31.359 --> 00:43:33.476
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING]

776
00:43:45.657 --> 00:43:48.135
Thanks for helping me close.

777
00:43:48.159 --> 00:43:49.937
DAPHNE: Oh. yeah.

778
00:43:49.961 --> 00:43:52.606
I broke a lot of things today.

779
00:43:52.630 --> 00:43:54.875
It's the least I can do.

780
00:43:54.899 --> 00:43:58.011
Well. I'm sure you'll
make it up to me.

781
00:43:58.035 --> 00:44:00.570
I'm sure I will.

782
00:44:04.342 --> 00:44:07.187
Mm. Nice.

783
00:44:07.211 --> 00:44:08.989
You run a little hot.

784
00:44:09.013 --> 00:44:10.958
Yeah.

785
00:44:10.982 --> 00:44:14.328
Everybody else is 98.6.

786
00:44:14.352 --> 00:44:16.664
but I'm always around 100. 101.

787
00:44:16.688 --> 00:44:20.584
Me too. It's a shifter thing.

788
00:44:20.608 --> 00:44:23.275
Yeah? I never knew.

789
00:44:25.262 --> 00:44:28.609
I can't believe I'm the
first one you've ever met.

790
00:44:28.633 --> 00:44:32.818
I mean. we're not common.
but we are out there.

791
00:44:34.005 --> 00:44:36.850
Ran into a few werewolves. Ugh.

792
00:44:36.874 --> 00:44:39.975
But nobody like us.

793
00:44:43.081 --> 00:44:46.365
What's it feel like
when you change?

794
00:44:49.570 --> 00:44:51.866
Like sparks

795
00:44:51.890 --> 00:44:54.935
running all over my skin.

796
00:44:54.959 --> 00:44:57.571
Used to scare
the shit out of me.

797
00:44:57.595 --> 00:45:00.140
Mm-hm. Me too.

798
00:45:00.164 --> 00:45:02.376
But now it just feels awesome.

799
00:45:02.400 --> 00:45:05.612
Yeah. and there's...
There's sort of a build.

800
00:45:05.636 --> 00:45:08.404
like a pressure.

801
00:45:09.807 --> 00:45:12.041
Where does it start?

802
00:45:15.280 --> 00:45:17.775
Here?

803
00:45:17.799 --> 00:45:21.934
Maybe...? Maybe here?

804
00:45:23.471 --> 00:45:26.216
Probably here. isn't it?

805
00:45:26.240 --> 00:45:27.735
That's where it hits me.

806
00:45:27.759 --> 00:45:32.139
Yeah. that's it.
right about there.

807
00:45:32.163 --> 00:45:36.449
Sparks start flying inside too.

808
00:45:39.086 --> 00:45:43.000
And you feel all lit up
like a broke power cable.

809
00:45:43.024 --> 00:45:45.168
Or a Christmas tree.

810
00:45:45.192 --> 00:45:50.262
And you just explode.

811
00:45:51.449 --> 00:45:53.382
[MOANING]

812
00:46:18.342 --> 00:46:20.454
Well. are you gonna
say it or should I?

813
00:46:20.478 --> 00:46:24.074
Say what?

814
00:46:24.098 --> 00:46:26.398
Nice rack.

815
00:46:27.668 --> 00:46:30.135
Nice balls.

816
00:46:38.229 --> 00:46:41.308
I have to ask a
question. Human stuff.

817
00:46:41.332 --> 00:46:43.933
I'll wait for you
at the elevator.

818
00:46:51.643 --> 00:46:55.189
Excuse me. is Barry the
bellboy working tonight?

819
00:46:55.213 --> 00:46:57.458
No. I'm sorry. Barry quit today.

820
00:46:57.482 --> 00:46:58.714
What?

821
00:47:00.235 --> 00:47:03.703
Oh. shoot.

822
00:47:05.273 --> 00:47:07.206
Thanks.

823
00:47:17.835 --> 00:47:20.269
TARA: Are you waiting up for me?

824
00:47:22.907 --> 00:47:25.374
I guess I am.

825
00:47:32.884 --> 00:47:36.197
Rough night?

826
00:47:36.221 --> 00:47:38.321
Really rough.

827
00:47:41.058 --> 00:47:43.504
We looked at houses
today. We didn't find anything.

828
00:47:43.528 --> 00:47:46.406
but don't worry. we'll
be out by morning.

829
00:47:46.430 --> 00:47:48.408
I filled the fridge with
your favorite things.

830
00:47:48.432 --> 00:47:50.249
and I made you dinner.

831
00:47:52.287 --> 00:47:54.465
Don't go.

832
00:47:54.489 --> 00:47:57.801
I'll call Sookie.

833
00:47:57.825 --> 00:48:00.069
I want you to stay.

834
00:48:00.093 --> 00:48:03.112
You're so good to me.

835
00:48:11.372 --> 00:48:14.006
You know why I'm good to you?

836
00:48:18.112 --> 00:48:21.425
Because you need it so much.

837
00:48:21.449 --> 00:48:25.067
And because it makes
you bloom like a flower.

838
00:48:26.670 --> 00:48:28.670
[SIGHS]

839
00:48:38.216 --> 00:48:39.927
Look at you.

840
00:48:39.951 --> 00:48:41.562
King of Sheba.

841
00:48:41.586 --> 00:48:43.686
Hey. baby.

842
00:48:49.660 --> 00:48:51.660
[GROANS]

843
00:48:54.181 --> 00:48:57.928
You saw them
in the lair tonight.

844
00:48:57.952 --> 00:49:00.630
Despicable.

845
00:49:00.654 --> 00:49:04.267
Vicious. petty. vile creatures.

846
00:49:04.291 --> 00:49:05.986
You're different.

847
00:49:06.010 --> 00:49:08.905
You're not like them.

848
00:49:08.929 --> 00:49:11.774
Bill. you're not.

849
00:49:11.798 --> 00:49:14.411
You have a heart.

850
00:49:14.435 --> 00:49:17.114
whether it beats or not.

851
00:49:17.138 --> 00:49:18.982
You can love.

852
00:49:19.006 --> 00:49:23.920
There wasn't one other vampire
there that could say the same.

853
00:49:23.944 --> 00:49:28.191
Let's slip away back
to Bon Temps right now.

854
00:49:28.215 --> 00:49:31.628
Let them devour each
other and leave us alone.

855
00:49:31.652 --> 00:49:34.231
You know we can't do that.

856
00:49:34.255 --> 00:49:38.068
Stan's as nutty as
a fruitcake. and...

857
00:49:38.092 --> 00:49:41.060
I gave my word to Eric.

858
00:49:45.183 --> 00:49:47.828
If anything happens
to you in that church. I...

859
00:49:47.852 --> 00:49:49.797
Don't say it.

860
00:49:49.821 --> 00:49:53.500
Don't even think it.

861
00:49:53.524 --> 00:49:57.459
I'll be in and out. easy-peasy.

862
00:50:00.031 --> 00:50:02.798
Oh. Bill.

863
00:50:12.776 --> 00:50:15.922
It's been a long night.

864
00:50:15.946 --> 00:50:18.459
Don't feel like you have to.

865
00:50:18.483 --> 00:50:22.229
Quit talking crazy.

866
00:50:22.253 --> 00:50:25.466
I just meant that...

867
00:50:25.490 --> 00:50:28.335
I'd be satisfied to
simply hold you.

868
00:50:28.359 --> 00:50:32.306
Well. I would not be satisfied.

869
00:50:32.330 --> 00:50:34.529
Not one bit.

870
00:50:37.101 --> 00:50:41.114
Then what do you want. Sookie?

871
00:50:41.138 --> 00:50:43.550
Say it.

872
00:50:43.574 --> 00:50:47.421
I want you.

873
00:50:47.445 --> 00:50:50.112
Every which way.

874
00:50:51.315 --> 00:50:55.362
I just want you.

875
00:50:55.386 --> 00:50:57.386
[♪♪♪]

876
00:51:10.718 --> 00:51:12.718
[♪♪♪]

877
00:51:17.491 --> 00:51:19.491
[BILL & SOOKIE PANTING]

878
00:51:35.176 --> 00:51:37.843
SOOKIE: Oh. Bill.

879
00:51:42.266 --> 00:51:44.266
[♪♪♪]

879
00:51:45.305 --> 00:52:45.335
